Perfect! I now have the rental information for both scenarios. Here's a detailed comparison of car rental prices for a 24-hour rental at the San Diego Marriott La Jolla:

## **Price Comparison Results**

**📅 Scenario 1: October 14-15 (Tomorrow → Next Day)**
**📅 Scenario 2: October 15-16 (Day After Tomorrow → Following Day)**

Both scenarios show **identical pricing** across all vehicle categories:

### **Available Vehicles & Pricing:**

| **Car Type** | **Vehicle** | **Both Scenarios Price** | **Difference** |
|-------------|-------------|-------------------------|----------------|
| **Economy** | Hyundai Veloster | **$58.70** | $0.00 |
| **Compact** | Nissan Versa | **$60.64** | $0.00 |
| **Intermediate** | Toyota Corolla | **$64.60** | $0.00 |
| **Premium** | Polestar 2 (Electric) | **$103.34** | $0.00 |

### **Key Findings:**

✅ **No price difference** between the two pickup dates
✅ **Same vehicles available** for both time periods  
✅ **All rentals include:**
- Unlimited mileage
- Free cancellation
- Air conditioning
- Automatic transmission

### **Recommendation:**

Since there's no price advantage to either date, you can choose based on your personal schedule preferences. All options are available through **Hertz** at the San Diego Marriott La Jolla location with the same terms and conditions.

The **Economy Hyundai Veloster at $58.70** offers the best value for a basic 24-hour rental, while the **Premium Polestar 2 at $103.34** provides a luxury electric vehicle experience if you prefer something more upscale.

My reservation was for Volkswagen Tiguan. 
The definition of this car category was:  MID size SUV with a capacity for 3 Large bags. 
Europcar gave me Cupra Formentor which is by any standard a small SUV or not an SUV at all.
If you look at the range of Cupra/Seat, the Ateca is the equivalent in size (mid SUV) and the Formentor is below it. 
Furthermore, There is absolutely no room for  3 Large bags (as reserved) in the Formentor.
I have pictures to support this.
Europcar were willing to change the car to station wagon to solve the 3 Large bags mismatch

messages.content:
Excellent news! I found plenty of car rental options available at San Diego International Airport for your business trip. Here's what I discovered:

## **Car Rental Availability** 🚗

**Both October 10th and 11th have great availability:**
- **85 rental cars available** for each date
- Pick-up/Drop-off: 8:00 PM at San Diego International Airport
- Rental period: 7 days (until October 17th, 8:00 PM)

## **Available Suppliers (Non-Dollar Options):**

### **1. Hertz** ⭐ 8.1/10 (102 reviews)
- **Nissan Versa (Compact)**: $318.04 for 7 days
- **Strengths:**
  - Excellent drop-off speed (9.1/10)
  - Good car cleanliness (8.4/10)
  - Good pick-up speed (8.2/10)
- **Areas for improvement:**
  - Helpfulness (7.4/10)
  - Value for money (7.7/10)

### **2. Avis** ⭐ 8.1/10 (291 reviews)
- **Chrysler Town & Country (Full-size/7-seater)**: $598.59 for 7 days
- **Strengths:**
  - Excellent drop-off speed (9.2/10)
  - Very good helpfulness (8.6/10)
  - Good car cleanliness (8.5/10)
- **Areas for improvement:**
  - Pick-up speed (7.2/10)
  - Value for money (7.0/10)

## **Recent Customer Feedback for Avis:**
- ✅ **Positive:** "Very Good Service", hybrid cars available, helpful staff
- ⚠️ **Watch out for:** Additional charges may apply, some cleanliness issues reported

### **Other Available Suppliers:**
- **Europcar** (12 vehicles available)
- **Sixt** (16 vehicles available)

## **Recommendation:**
Both dates have excellent availability! **Hertz offers better value for money** if you need a compact car, while **Avis provides larger vehicles** if you need more space for business materials or colleagues. Both have similar overall ratings (8.1/10) and very good drop-off speeds.

## **Pricing Range**
- Most rentals fall in the $50-$150 per day range
- Sample prices for a 7-day rental (Nov 20-27):
  - Intermediate cars: ~$560-680
  - Full-size cars: ~$765

## **Dollar Car Rental Reviews**

Since you asked specifically about non-Avis suppliers, here are the detailed reviews for **Dollar**:

messages.content:
Great news! I found plenty of car rental availability at Chicago O'Hare International Airport for both dates you're considering. Here's what I found:

## **Car Availability Summary**

### **December 10th, 2024 (Tomorrow) - Pickup 4:00 PM**
✅ **Available** - 220+ rental options from multiple suppliers
- **Price range**: $293.78 - $340.62 (7-day rental)
- **Primary supplier**: Dollar (multiple vehicle classes available)
- **Vehicle options**: Economy (Chevrolet Spark), Compact, Intermediate (Nissan Sentra, Toyota RAV4), Standard (Volkswagen Jetta), Full-size

### **December 11th, 2024 (Day After Tomorrow) - Pickup 4:00 PM** 
✅ **Available** - 220+ rental options from multiple suppliers  
- **Price range**: $298.02 - $426.56 (6-day rental)
- **Suppliers**: Dollar + **Hertz** (non-Dollar option!)
- **Vehicle options**: Similar range plus larger SUVs from Hertz

## **Non-Dollar Supplier Reviews: Hertz**

Since you wanted reviews for suppliers other than Dollar, here's what customers are saying about **Hertz** at O'Hare:

**Overall Rating**: 7.9/10 ("Good") based on 475 reviews

**Detailed Breakdown**:
- **Drop-off speed**: 9.6/10 (Excellent)
- **Car cleanliness**: 8.0/10 (Very Good)  
- **Helpfulness**: 7.8/10 (Good)
- **Pick-up speed**: 7.2/10 (Good)
- **Value for money**: 6.9/10 (Decent)

**Recent Customer Feedback**:
- **Positive**: "Better than expected! Drop off was a breeze", "The counter lady was really friendly and helpful"
- **Concerns**: Some customers reported unexpected additional charges and longer wait times
- **Mixed**: Car cleanliness can vary, though generally rated well

**Hertz Options Available (Dec 11th)**:
- **Dodge Grand Caravan** (7-seater): $426.56
- **Ford Expedition** (7-seater SUV): $420.03

## **Recommendation**

Both dates have excellent availability! **December 11th** offers more variety with Hertz as an alternative to Dollar. Hertz scores slightly higher overall (7.9/10 vs 7.7/10) and excels in drop-off efficiency, which is great for airport returns.

**All rentals include**:
- Unlimited mileage
- Free cancellation
- Automatic transmission
- Air conditioning
- Shuttle bus service from terminals

Would you like me to help you compare specific vehicle models or get more details about any particular option?

messages.content:
Excellent news! I found plenty of car rental availability at Seattle-Tacoma International Airport for both dates. Here's what I discovered:

## **Car Availability Summary**

✅ **Both November 25th and November 26th, 2024 have 75+ rental cars available**
- Pick-up: 3:00 PM 
- Return: December 2nd, 2024 at 3:00 PM
- All vehicles include unlimited mileage and free cancellation

## **Available Suppliers (excluding Hertz):**

### **1. Budget Rental Cars** 
- **Rating: 7.1/10 (Good) - 698 reviews**
- **Price Range:** From ~$607/week
- **Vehicle Example:** Dodge Grand Caravan (Full-size, 7 seats)
- **Location:** Car Rental Centre at the airport

**Customer Review Insights:**
- **Strengths:** Clean cars (8.1/10), very fast drop-off (9.6/10)
- **Weaknesses:** Very slow pick-up process (4.0/10) - customers report 1.5-3 hour wait times
- **Recent feedback:** Some customers experienced unexpected charges and long queues

### **2. Avis**
- **Rating: 7.3/10 (Good) - 263 reviews**  
- **Price Range:** From ~$631/week
- **Vehicle Example:** Chrysler Town & Country (Full-size, 7 seats)
- **Location:** Car Rental Centre at the airport
- **Pick-up time rating:** 4.5/10, Drop-off: 9.4/10

### **3. Sixt**
- **16 vehicles available**
- Limited details in current search

## **Recommendation:**

Both dates are equally viable for availability. **November 26th might be slightly better** as it avoids the busy travel period right after Thanksgiving weekend (November 25th is the day after Thanksgiving).

**For supplier choice:** Avis has a slightly higher overall rating (7.3 vs 7.1) and better pick-up speed than Budget, though both have similar challenges with airport pick-up times.

Would you like me to search for more details on Sixt vehicles or help you with any other aspects of your Seattle business trip planning?

## **Option 1: Chevrolet Cruze (Intermediate Class)**

### **Pricing & Basic Info**
- **Total Cost**: $684.06 for 7 days
- **Car Class**: Intermediate
- **Supplier**: Avis (6.6/10 rating - "OK" with 240 reviews)
- **Free Cancellation**: Up to 48 hours before pickup

### **Vehicle Specifications**
- **Seats**: 5 passengers
- **Doors**: 2/4 doors
- **Transmission**: Automatic
- **Air Conditioning**: Yes
- **Mileage**: Unlimited
- **Luggage Capacity**: 1 small suitcase + 1 big suitcase

### **What's Included**
- Collision Damage Waiver (CDW)
- Theft Cover
- Third-Party Liability (TPL)
- Free cancellation up to 48 hours before pickup

---

## **Option 2: Ford Escape (Intermediate Class)**

### **Pricing & Basic Info**
- **Total Cost**: $821.09 for 7 days
- **Car Class**: Intermediate
- **Supplier**: Avis (6.6/10 rating - "OK" with 240 reviews)
- **Free Cancellation**: Up to 48 hours before pickup

### **Vehicle Specifications**
- **Seats**: 5 passengers
- **Doors**: 4 doors
- **Transmission**: Automatic
- **Air Conditioning**: Yes
- **Mileage**: Unlimited
- **Luggage Capacity**: 3 big suitcases (more spacious than Cruze)

### **What's Included**
- Collision Damage Waiver (CDW)
- Theft Cover
- Third-Party Liability (TPL)
- Free cancellation up to 48 hours before pickup

---

## **Key Differences**

1. **Price**: The Chevrolet Cruze is $137 cheaper than the Ford Escape
2. **Luggage Space**: The Ford Escape offers significantly more cargo space (3 big suitcases vs 1 big + 1 small)
3. **Vehicle Type**: The Escape is an SUV offering higher seating position and better road visibility, while the Cruze is a sedan

## **Pickup & Drop-off Details**
- **Pickup**: Denver International Airport via shuttle bus (Stand #4 at shuttle pickup zone)
- **Drop-off**: Salt Lake City International Airport (in-terminal location)
- **Deposit Required**: $250 (refundable)

## **Available Extras** (same for both vehicles):
- Additional driver: $65
- Child seats/booster seats: $87 each
- GPS navigation: $135.92

**Recommendation**: If Lily needs more luggage space for a week-long trip, the Ford Escape would be the better choice despite the higher cost. If she's traveling light and wants to save money, the Chevrolet Cruze is an excellent value option.

reviews.negative:
The verbal FREE upgrade offered by agent Sybille, (due to a last-minute cancellation) was subsequently amended to a "choice upgrade' at an extra cost of CHF 74.28/day (x12 days), i.e. CHF 891.36 more than agreed through you. (that's C$1,488.57, i.e. 367% more than the basic rental prepaid through rentalcars.com!!! (that excessive rental cost noted above is exclusive of the 8.10% VAT, and the "Premium Location Fee" of 20%, which was not noted on the rentalcars.com agreement.  - not holding it against you....but SixT certainly lives up to its worldwide reputation as untrust-worthy rental company.
When they emailed me a request to rate their service, I told them loud and clear that unless they amend the final charge upon return of the vehicle, I'll see them in court.
The credit-card pre-authorization (Security Deposit) of CHF 1,463.56 was cancelled/withdrawn two days before end of rental, but to this day, I don't know what they debited to my credit-card, as there is still no Sixt debit showing on my Visa account.
That said, I had also purchased a CDW through rentalcoverage.com, the confirmation of which I showed to the SixT agent upon pickup (she did not take the details), but upon return of the vehicle they claimed that I damaged the rear-left wheel rim (5-10 cms down to primer); when I told the receiving agent that I a) have CDW coverage and b) had taken photos at time of pickup, which clearly shows the pre-existing damage, she noted it on the Return-Receipt, but I am now being hounded by the SixT-Damage dept. (As I'm still travelling, I have had no time to respond, and frankly see no reason why I should respond to that department.
Last, but not least, Sixt's Diamond member should not be permitted to push through a line of 12 people waiting to be served, when there is no dedicated Diamond-Member counter.
Decency toward the common-mortals is sorely lacking at Sixt!
PS: I've rented cars through rentalcars.com previously and everything went without a hitch....s
reviews.positive:
Originally, I appreciated the offer of a FREE upgrade to a BMW x2, however that pleasure was short-lived (see 'what you didn't like').
This slightly larger vehicle was good to drive, but had useless gadgets which made driving in darkness outright dangerous. I did like the automatic transmission and the heads-up display, though. The fuel-mileage was great too.
The SIXT rental desk is easily located and car condition is good
reviews.negative: The SIXT representative keen to push me to upgrade my car (which required CHF 50 per day) and insurance.  After my rejection, I was  told to wait 30min as my booked needed more time to do cleaning.  I booked the car at 2pm; I finally got the car (same size/group; but not my )
The gas tank was not completely full.  Not quite what I expected from Sixt.
The cost of additional full protection of insurance is quite high
reviews.positive: Sixt is my rental car choice

We complained and we did not get a result even after a week. This rental is currently the worst we´ve had.

We booked this company because they had a specific car model (Fiat Abarth), but we doubt they even have this model, we were disappointed that we could not get this car model.

Perfect! I've found the detailed information for all vehicles. Based on my analysis, here's what I found regarding vehicles with snow chains for your Berlin to Zurich Christmas journey:

## **Vehicle with Snow Chains INCLUDED:**

### **Volkswagen T-Roc (Compact) - US$892.95**
- **✅ WINTERISATION FEE INCLUDED** - This means snow chains and winter equipment are already included in the price
- **Pickup:** Berlin - Brandenburger Tor (Christmas Eve, Dec 24, 12:00)
- **Drop-off:** Zurich - Maschinenstrasse (Boxing Day, Dec 26, 12:00)
- **Supplier:** Sixt (rated 8.0/10 - Very Good)
- **Features:** Manual transmission, 5 seats, 4 doors, air conditioning
- **Mileage:** 600 km included
- **Total Price:** US$892.95 (includes all taxes, fees & winter equipment)

## **Vehicles where Snow Chains are Available as Extras:**

### **Polestar 2 (Full-size, Electric) - US$834.48 + US$37.44 for snow chains**
- **Snow chains available for:** Additional US$37.44
- **Winter tyres available for:** Additional US$39.64  
- **Features:** Fully electric, automatic transmission, larger vehicle
- **Total with snow chains:** US$871.92

The **Opel Mokka** doesn't offer snow chains as an option.

## **Recommendation:**
The **Volkswagen T-Roc** is your best option since it already includes the winterisation fee (snow chains and winter equipment) in the base price of US$892.95. This is perfect for your winter drive through Germany and Switzerland, especially during Christmas when snow conditions are likely on Alpine routes.

## **Car Rental Options with Snow Chains Available**

### **1. Toyota Aygo (Mini) - Madrid Plaza Espana**
- **Pickup:** Friday, Dec 20 · 12:00 - Madrid Plaza Espana
- **Drop-off:** Sunday, Dec 22 · 12:00 - Barcelona Las Ramblas
- **Supplier:** Alamo (Rating: 8.3/10 - Very Good)
- **Base Rental Price:** $162.09 USD (2 days)
- **Snow Chains Add-on:** $58.85 USD for the rental period
- **Total with Snow Chains:** $220.94 USD
- **Vehicle Features:** 4 seats, 3 doors, manual transmission, air conditioning, unlimited mileage
- **Includes:** Free cancellation, CDW, theft cover, TPL

### **2. Toyota Aygo (Mini) - Madrid Train Station**
- **Pickup:** Friday, Dec 20 · 12:00 - Madrid Train Station (Atocha)
- **Drop-off:** Sunday, Dec 22 · 12:00 - Barcelona Las Ramblas
- **Supplier:** Alamo (Rating: 7.9/10 - Good)
- **Base Rental Price:** $162.09 USD (2 days)
- **Snow Chains Add-on:** $58.85 USD for the rental period
- **Total with Snow Chains:** $220.94 USD
- **Vehicle Features:** Same as above - 4 seats, 3 doors, manual transmission, air conditioning
- **Includes:** Free cancellation, CDW, theft cover, TPL

### **3. Seat Alhambra (Full-size) - Madrid Plaza Espana**
- **Pickup:** Friday, Dec 20 · 12:00 - Madrid Plaza Espana
- **Drop-off:** Sunday, Dec 22 · 12:00 - Barcelona Las Ramblas
- **Supplier:** Alamo (Rating: 8.3/10 - Very Good)
- **Base Rental Price:** $373.49 USD (2 days)
- **Snow Chains Add-on:** $58.85 USD for the rental period
- **Total with Snow Chains:** $432.34 USD
- **Vehicle Features:** 7 seats, 4 doors, automatic transmission, air conditioning, unlimited mileage
- **Includes:** Free cancellation, CDW, theft cover, TPL

## **Key Points:**
- **Snow chains cost:** $58.85 USD for the entire rental period across all vehicles
- **All vehicles** offer unlimited mileage and free cancellation up to 48 hours before pickup
- **Payment:** You'll pay today in INR, with a small one-way fee (€0.01) payable at pickup in EUR
- **Winter driving:** Snow chains are perfect for your December travel, especially if you encounter snowy conditions in the Pyrenees region between Madrid and Barcelona

The Toyota Aygo options are budget-friendly, while the Seat Alhambra offers more space and comfort for your road trip adventure!

Based on my search for car rentals from Frankfurt to Berlin for November 10-14, 2024, here's a summary of the vehicle options regarding snow chains:

## 🚗 Car Rental Summary: Frankfurt to Berlin
**Dates:** November 10-14, 2024 (3 PM pickup/dropoff)  
**Total Results:** 177 vehicles available

## ❄️ Snow Chain Availability:

Unfortunately, **none of the vehicles include snow chains in their base rental price**. However, snow chains are available as **optional extras** for most vehicles:

### 1. **MG MG5 (Compact, Fully Electric)** - $405.21
- **Snow chains:** Available for +$73.84 per rental
- **Winter tyres:** Available for +$78.16 per rental  
- **Features:** Automatic transmission, 5 seats, 4 doors
- **Supplier:** Sixt (6.6/10 rating)

### 2. **Volkswagen Polo (Economy)** - $391.83  
- **Snow chains:** Available for +$73.84 per rental
- **Winter tyres:** Available for +$78.16 per rental
- **Features:** Manual transmission, 5 seats, 4 doors
- **Supplier:** Sixt (6.6/10 rating)

### 3. **Fiat 500 (Mini)** - $387.33
- **Special note:** "Price includes winterisation fee" 
- This may include winter equipment, but I couldn't get detailed information

## 💡 Recommendation:
Since you specifically want snow chains, I'd recommend:
1. **Budget option:** Fiat 500 with winterisation fee included ($387.33)
2. **Comfort option:** Add snow chains to either the MG MG5 or Volkswagen Polo

The snow chain extras cost $73.84 per rental, so your total would be around $465-479 with snow chains included on the compact or economy cars.

Would you like me to get more details about any specific vehicle or look for additional options?

## Summary of Car Rental Options with Baby Seats 🚗👶

Great news! I found **2 vehicles** available for your Warsaw to Krakow trip that offer baby seats. Here's your complete summary:

---

### **Option 1: Renault Clio (Economy) - Express**
**📍 Route:** Warsaw Train Station → Krakow Train Station  
**💰 Total Price:** ~$92.35 USD  
- Base rental: $55.08 (pay today)
- One-way fee: $37.27 (pay at pickup)

**👶 Baby Seat Options Available:**
- **Baby seat:** $7.46 - For babies up to 9 kg/20 lbs (about 1 year old)
- **Child seat:** $7.46 - For small children 9-18 kg/20-40 lbs (1-3 years old)  
- **Booster seat:** $4.96 - For bigger children 18-45 kg/40-100 lbs (4-11 years old)
- Up to 2 seats of each type available

**📅 Dates:** Thu, Nov 28 at 1:00 PM → Sat, Nov 30 at 1:00 PM (2 days)  
**⭐ Rating:** 6.5/10 (129 reviews) - "OK"  
**✅ Includes:** Free cancellation, CDW, theft cover, unlimited mileage

---

### **Option 2: Renault Clio (Economy) - Express**
**📍 Route:** Warsaw - Zachodnia Train Station → Krakow - Plaszow Train Station  
**💰 Total Price:** ~$92.35 USD  
- Base rental: $55.08 (pay today)
- One-way fee: $37.27 (pay at pickup)

**👶 Baby Seat Options Available:**
- **Baby seat:** $7.46 - For babies up to 9 kg/20 lbs (about 1 year old)
- **Child seat:** $7.46 - For small children 9-18 kg/20-40 lbs (1-3 years old)
- **Booster seat:** $4.96 - For bigger children 18-45 kg/40-100 lbs (4-11 years old)
- Up to 2 seats of each type available

**📅 Dates:** Thu, Nov 28 at 1:00 PM → Sat, Nov 30 at 1:00 PM (2 days)  
**⭐ Rating:** 6.6/10 (38 reviews) - "OK"  
**✅ Includes:** Free cancellation, CDW, theft cover, unlimited mileage

---

### **💡 Key Points:**
- Both vehicles are the same model (Renault Clio) from Express rental company
- Same pricing structure for both options
- Baby seat rental adds only $7.46 to your total cost
- Manual transmission, 5 seats, air conditioning
- All fees are clearly broken down with no hidden costs
- Credit card required at pickup

**Note:** The Kia Sportage option I found does NOT offer baby seats (only child seats for older kids), so these are your two best options for traveling with a baby! 🍼
